Castor Oil: Ricinus communis, another name for castor oil, is a nutrient-rich vegetable oil made from castor beans. Castor oil helps to moisturise and hydrate the hair and scalp. It includes significant amounts of ricinoleic acid, an important amino acid that works as a natural moisturiser for hair. Omega 6 and Omega 9 fatty acids are also high, which give the hair moisture-retaining strength. Castor oil enhances hair shine and minimizes abnormal hair loss. Vitamin E and fatty acids found in castor oil are good for the health of your hair. In order to maintain a proper cycle of growth and regrowth for your hair, it also aids in protein synthesis. Castor oil also helps in the treatment of dandruff. Coconut Milk: Coconut milk is one of the best and most effective remedies for natural hair growth because it is rich in iron, potassium and essential fats. A key component of coconut is lauric acid. Its moderate fatty acid is renowned for its ability to penetrate hair easily and enhance cuticle strength. The high protein content of coconut milk may help to maintain the strength of the hair. 